OL,5,Ccontroversy
OL,7,FThe Government-owned company was
OL,8,Fpreviously criticised for converting
OL,9,Fthe main concourse departures board
OL,10,Finto a large advertising screen, with
OL,11,Fsmaller train information boards
OL,12,Finstalled elsewhere.
OL,14,FMs Haigh's successor, Heidi Alexander,
OL,15,Fsaid: "I'm pleased to see Network Rail
OL,16,Ftaking action and making progress on
OL,17,Fits five-point plan to alleviate some
OL,18,Fof the issues faced at Euston `
OL,19,Fparticularly at this time of year,
OL,20,Fwhen the festive period brings an
OL,21,Fincrease in passengers.
